Hangman Game in Python

A Hangman Game is a classic word-guessing game where the player tries to guess
a hidden word one letter at a time within a limited number of incorrect attempts.
It is a popular beginner-friendly Python project because it demonstrates core
programming concepts such as loops, conditional statements, strings, lists, functions, and randomization.

How the Game Works
Select a Random Word: The program randomly chooses a word from a predefined list.
Display Hidden Word: The selected word is displayed as underscores (_), with each underscore representing an unguessed letter.
Player Guesses a Letter: The user enters one letter at a time.

Check the Guess:
If the guessed letter is correct, all matching positions in the word are revealed.
If the guess is incorrect, the player loses one attempt.
Repeat the Process: The game continues until the player guesses the complete word or runs out of attempts.
Game Over: The program displays whether the player has won or lost and reveals the correct word if necessary.

Features
Random word selection
Letter-by-letter guessing
Limited incorrect attempts
Tracks guessed letters
Displays the current progress after each guess
Win and lose conditions
Beginner-friendly and interactive gameplay
Python Concepts Used
random module for selecting words
Loops (while and for)
Conditional statements (if, elif, else)
Lists and strings
User input with input()
Functions for better code organization

Advantages
Improves logical thinking and problem-solving skills.
Helps beginners understand Python fundamentals.
Easy to customize by adding difficulty levels, hints, categories, or graphical interfaces.
Provides hands-on experience with user interaction and game development.

Conclusion
The Hangman Game is an excellent Python project for beginners, combining programming fundamentals
with interactive gameplay. It strengthens concepts like loops, conditions, string manipulation,
and random selection while providing an engaging way to practice coding and build confidence in Python development.
